ion reliable / fall back to a cheap branch resolution so a turn on a known branch never gets empty observed_targets; and (b) back-fill association at the session level when the branch/PR becomes known, so turns captured before the PR existed still appear. Don't just paper over it in the projection.\n4. Verify with the report's checklist: after a fresh capture, every turn of an on-branch session is indexed under that branch's ref: target, and project_pr for the PR returns turns spanning the whole session including the first prompt.\n\nGotcha (from the report): the append-log records set_add with value \"[]\" as a canonical form — that is NOT the member list (the real members are in set_values, joined via rowid). Don't let that mislead you. Keep changes minimal and add tests.\n","prompt_source":"spawned_agent","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-25T14:42:54.443Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}